answers.answer: Protein in urine is dangerous when you have high blood pressure. Then you would have preeclampsia. When you have trace or a little protein but not high bp your fine its not preeclampsia...so your body is just preparing for labor your fine

question: i am almost 38 weeks pregnant, not feeling well today, i have lots of cramping, but not contractions.  I am nauseous, and have had diarrhea, lost some of my plug this morning.  i had a doctors appointment, i am 75% effaced and i am 2-3cm dilated.  my blood pressure is good, it has never been high. but I am very swollen and have been for a few weeks.  would the protein in my urine mean that labor is near? they didnt seem concerned about it because it was only a little bit.
